-- 
2011-02-28T19:44:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/petrobras-to-invest-706-million-in-third-liquefied-gas-plant.html
  Petroleo Brasileiro SA ,  Brazil â€™s
state-controlled oil company, said it will invest $706 million
in a liquefied natural gas terminal in the northeast state of
Bahia, the third plant to be built in the South American nation.  The plant will have the capacity to process 14 million
cubic meters of natural gas a day and is expected to start in
September 2013, the company known as Petrobras  said  today in a
statement. Rio de Janeiro-based Petrobras said it will sign a
memorandum of intent with the Bahian government tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
